  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD model employs a steady-state, single-phase incompressible Navier-Stokes solver with a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. Blood is treated as a homogeneous Newtonian fluid; the two-phase plasma-cell interaction and viscoelastic non-Newtonian shear-thinning behaviour present in real CPB blood are excluded from the model formulation on the basis that their contribution to bulk hemolysis index is expected to be secondary at the high-shear operating regime of interest. No fidelity trade study quantifying the error introduced by these exclusions has been conducted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-worst-case-ident",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-cpb-cou1",
