      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, operating range, and fluid properties sufficiently representative of COU device and operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same platform as the COU device. Operating points span the 5 flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Fluid properties match bulk Newtonian viscosity of blood at 37°C. The validation is considered representative of the COU operating envelope. Note: both the validation experiments and the CFD model employ Newtonian single-phase fluid assumptions; the non-Newtonian shear-thinning and two-phase plasma-cell coupling present in actual CPB blood are absent from both, so the validation does not probe the fidelity gap introduced by those modelling abstractions. This is considered acceptable because the effect is expected to be secondary at high shear rates characteristic of CPB operation.",
