      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified for the COU operating regime.",
      "rationale": "Steady-state RANS (SST k-omega) turbulence model selected based on published literature for rotary blood pump CFD at MRL 2. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) adopted as the standard for FDA-submission analyses. Blood treated as homogeneous Newtonian fluid; non-Newtonian shear-thinning and two-phase plasma-cell coupling are excluded. The model documentation states these effects are secondary at the high-shear CPB regime (wall shear rates > 5000 s-1) but provides no quantitative sensitivity analysis or fidelity trade study to support this assertion. Requirement considered met at Level 1.",
