    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. Discretization error (GCI 2.7%) and output comparison (RH error ≤ 13.2%) are within pre-specified tolerances. The Newtonian single-phase modelling assumption is noted in the model form factor; the team accepts the assertion that non-Newtonian and two-phase effects are secondary at CPB operating shear rates, consistent with the validation evidence available. No dissenting opinions were recorded. The model is accepted for use in the COU as defined.",
